           <abstract>
               <p>Sends proboscis of a Sphinx-moth that is 22 cms long.</p>
               <p>Discusses eleven species of butterfly which visit <hi rend="italic">Lantana</hi>, a plant which blooms only for three days and whose flowers are yellow on the first day, orange on the second, and purple on the third. Most species only visit the flowers when they are yellow.</p>
                <p>Describes and draws the odiferous organs of a Sphinx-moth.</p>
               <p>Describes a secondary sexual character of several species of <hi rend="italic">Callidryas</hi> and other <hi rend="italic">Pierinæ</hi>: the costal margin of the anterior wing is sharply serrated in the males, while it is smooth in the females.</p>
            </abstract>
